## Required:
* Linux (test on Ubuntu 16.04)
* Install gcc 
* Install PBC 
* Install GMP 
* Install openssl 
* Edit the makefile (the first line) to have:
	LIBS_HOME  : the directory where you have installed PBC, GMP and openssl.


## To compile:
* No optimization: make -Ibuild
* Run test : make -Ibuild run < src/F_128.param


## Test scenario of the CDH-based POR scheme (the default is 128-bit security):
* The default parameters of elliptic curve are in the F_128.param file
* The test scenario is in the main.cpp file

## We include the built test in the default test scenario in bin. To run, use the command 'make -Ibuild run < src/F_128.param'
